methods.name: countContacts
methods.docs:
Count the number of contacts on the device.

Only available on Android and iOS.

methods.name: createContact
methods.docs:
Create a new contact on the device.

Only available on Android and iOS.

methods.name: createGroup
methods.docs:
Create a new contact group on the device.

Only available on iOS.

methods.name: deleteContactById
methods.docs:
Delete a contact from the device.

Only available on Android and iOS.

methods.name: deleteGroupById
methods.docs:
Delete a contact group from the device.

Only available on iOS.

methods.name: displayContactById
methods.docs:
Display an existing contact by identifier.

Only available on Android and iOS.

methods.name: displayCreateContact
methods.docs:
Open a native modal to create a new device contact.

This allows the user to update the contact information before saving it
and does not require any permissions.

Only available on Android and iOS.

methods.name: displayUpdateContactById
methods.docs:
Open a native modal to update a contact.

Only available on Android and iOS.

methods.name: getAccounts
methods.docs:
List all accounts on the device.

Only available on Android.

methods.name: getContactById
methods.docs:
Find a contact by identifier.

Only available on Android and iOS.

methods.name: getContacts
methods.docs:
List all contacts on the device.

Only available on Android and iOS.

methods.name: getGroupById
methods.docs:
Find a contact group by identifier.

Only available on iOS.

methods.name: getGroups
methods.docs:
List all contact groups on the device.

Only available on iOS.

methods.name: isAvailable
methods.docs: Check whether or not contacts is available on the device.

methods.name: isSupported
methods.docs: Check if the contacts API is available on the device.

methods.name: pickContact
methods.docs: Open the contact picker to select a contact from the device.

methods.name: pickContacts
methods.docs: Open the contact picker to select a contact from the device.

methods.name: updateContactById
methods.docs:
Update an existing contact on the device.

Only available on Android and iOS.

methods.name: checkPermissions
methods.docs:
Check permissions to access contacts.

Only available on Android and iOS.

methods.name: requestPermissions
methods.docs:
Request permissions to access contacts.

Only available on Android and iOS.
